# .gitignore
# ===========
# This file tells git which files and directories to ignore and never commit to the repository. This is important for two reasons:
# - keeping sensitive credentials like your bot token private
# - avoiding large auto-generated files that can always be recreated locally.

# Build output generated by cargo
# This directory is large and can always be recreated with cargo build
/target

# Your personal configuration file containing sensitive credentials
# Copy config.example.toml to config.toml and fill in your values
# Never commit this file! Your bot token must stay private.
config.toml
